.TH _PRINTF 3 "March 2026" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
_printf \- Custom made printf function
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "main.h"
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
_printf prints output based on the format string.
.B Format Specifiers:
.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.
.TP
.B %s
Prints a string of characters or (null) if string is NULL.
.TP
.B %d, %i
Prints integer in decimal notation.
.TP
.B %%
Prints a % sign.
.SH RETURN VALUE
_printf returns the number of characters printed, excluding the null byte to end output to strings.
Returns a negative value when an error occurs.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B Print a simple string:
_printf("Hello, World!\n");
.TP
.B Print a character:
_printf("%c\n", 'A');
.TP
.B Print a string:
_printf("%s\n", "Hello");
.TP
.B Print an integer:
_printf("%d\n", 42);
.TP
.B Print a percent sign:
_printf("100%%\n");
